   "source": [
    "#### 1. Scatter Plot for Age vs. Job Satisfaction\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Visualize the relationship between respondents' age (`Age`) and job satisfaction (`JobSatPoints_6`). Use this plot to identify any patterns or trends.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#clean and convert columns\n",
    "df_scatter = df[['Age', 'JobSatPoints_6']].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "df_scatter = df_scatter[df_scatter['Age'] != 'Prefer not to say']\n",
    "\n",
    "df_scatter['JobSatPoints_6'] = pd.to_numeric(\n",
    "    df_scatter['JobSatPoints_6'], errors='coerce'\n",
    ")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#convert age ranges\n",
    "age_mapping = {\n",
    "    'Under 18 years old': 16,\n",
    "    '18-24 years old': 21,\n",
    "    '25-34 years old': 30,\n",
    "    '35-44 years old': 40,\n",
    "    '45-54 years old': 50,\n",
    "    '55-64 years old': 60,\n",
    "    '65 years or older': 70\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "df_scatter['Age_numeric'] = df_scatter['Age'].map(age_mapping)\n",
    "\n",
    "df_scatter = df_scatter.dropna()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
